Canucks’ Raymond Has Broken Vertebra After Collision in Game 6 of Final

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-06-14T16:51:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/canucks-raymond-has-broken-vertebra-after-collision-in-game-6-of-final.html
Vancouver Canucks  left wing Mason
Raymond broke a vertebra last night in a collision in Game 6 of
the Stanley Cup Final against the  Boston Bruins , the team said
in a news release. He won’t be able to play for three to four
months.  The final game of the best-of-seven series is tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novywilliams in New York at 
 enovywilliam@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
